editorialNotes.tagline: A fun way to learn a language
editorialNotes.standard: With its friendly approach and awesome updates, Duolingo’s long been one of our favourite apps for learning another language. Its secret: making the process genuinely fun. Engaging mini-games test your reading, writing and speaking skills, and joining a club (where you can encourage and compete with others) adds a great social element. Bonus: all those languages and games are available for free!
editorialNotes.short: Learn a new language. Join a club, chat with bots and get reminders to practice.

editorialNotes.tagline: Learn and play in Toca’s world
editorialNotes.standard: This brings together all the Toca Life apps, letting your beloved characters from different apps mingle in one beautiful world–a world that keeps growing with new areas to explore and characters to meet.
editorialNotes.short: Enrich your child’s imagination through creative world-building.
Create and study flashcards and be ready for test day.

editorialNotes.standard: Improve your memory, writing, and reading comprehension with this powerful brain-training app via short, enjoyable mini games made to help strengthen key abilities and keep you motivated.
editorialNotes.short: Get a personalised training program for a better learning experience.

editorialNotes.standard: This futuristic app lets you point your camera at the problem, and a step-by-step explanation instantly appears on your screen! Triple-digit multiplication? Linear and quadratic inequalities? No problem.
editorialNotes.short: Solve your maths problems and get step-by-step explanations.

ios.subtitle: Learn at school, home or work

editorialNotes.standard: A winning blend of education app and game show, students can use their iPhone, iPad, or Mac to answer quiz questions in hopes of becoming the class brainiac—or create their own games to play (or study) at home.
editorialNotes.short: Create and participate in quizzes in Kahoot's fun and interactive way.

editorialNotes.tagline: Cook up a storm in the kitchen
editorialNotes.standard: Food’s fun for everyone with Toca Boca’s second go-round in the kitchen. Choose different characters and try to please their palates by preparing fish, fruit, vegetables, and more. Deciding what to serve and whether to bake, boil, fry, chop, puree, or season it—or all of the above—will keep young chefs happily cooking away.

editorialNotes.short: Identify flowers, plants and trees with your camera.

editorialNotes.standard: No time to read? Bestselling non-fiction books are condensed into bite-size summaries of 15 minutes or less. We especially love the audio-only feature for learning on the go.

Learn how to play piano with this app that listens to what you’re playing on any keyboard or piano–or lets you use an onscreen one. Within minutes you’ll be playing along with familiar songs, even if you’ve never touched a keyboard in your life.
editorialNotes.short: Personalised exercises, piano courses, hundreds of songs.

editorialNotes.standard: With Memrise, language learning’s a game—the irresistible kind that anyone can pick up and play. It teaches you everyday words and phrases—perfect for your next trip abroad—and reinforces them with fun quizzes and playful images. We get an awesome sense of progress every time we use it.
